# Renavest Financial Therapy Platform Guidelines

You are developing a financial therapy platform that balances quantitative data with emotional wellness. Follow these guidelines for effective implementation in Cursor.

## Core Design Principles
- **Balance Dual Domains**: Implement both financial analytics and emotional support features.
- **Prioritize Privacy**: Create robust security and consent-driven data sharing.
- **User Experience First**: Design non-judgmental, psychologically safe interfaces.

## Feature Implementation
### Client Dashboard
- Implement visual goal trackers with progress indicators
- Create money beliefs/scripts displays connected to behavior patterns
- Build emotional check-in system aligned with payroll periods
- Develop non-judgmental spending pattern insights
- Include educational resources with simple explanations

### Therapist Dashboard
- Build structured notes system (pre/during/post meeting)
- Implement consent-driven client financial overview
- Create resource library with customizable worksheets
- Develop alert system for concerning patterns
- Include business analytics for income tracking

## Data Handling & API Design
- Implement secure financial connections with manual fallbacks
- Create granular privacy controls at account level
- Build resilient data aggregation with health monitoring
- Use AI to enhance (never replace) human connection
- Process sensitive data locally when possible

## Mobile-First Implementation
- Design responsive interfaces with Tailwind breakpoints
- Start with mobile layouts, then expand to larger screens
- Test across multiple device sizes and orientations
- Ensure all critical functions work on mobile devices

